Data Visualisation with ggplot2 Project Joseph Thiongo

AfterWork Data Science: Data Visualisation with Python Project

1. Defining the Question

a) Specifying the Data Analysis Question

To provide Hilton management with strategy recommendations that will lead to revenue growth.

b) Defining the Metric for Success

The solutions to the following questions will help us answer our research question:

  • When is the best time of year to book a hotel room?
  • When is the optimal length of stay in order to get the best daily rate?
  • How will you know if a hotel was likely to receive a disproportionately high number of special requests?

c) Understanding the context

I am a Data Scientist working for Hilton International Hotels and need to help the management decide on the strategies that will lead to revenue growth.

I have a dataset containing information on the various chain of hotels, including when customers made the booking, length of stay, the number of adults, children, or babies, and the number of available parking spaces, among other things.

Given this dataset, i will perform data exploration, data cleaning, and analysis to come with appropriate recommendations. As a start, while performing data analysis, i will ask the following questions from the given dataset. Making sure to have a visualization for each question. How many bookings were canceled? What was the booking ratio between resort hotels and city hotels? What was the percentage of booking for each year? Which was the busiest month for hotels? Most guests came from which country? How long do most people stay in hotels? Which was the most booked accommodation type (Single, Couple, Family)?

d) Recording the Experimental Design

The steps to be taken include:

  • Load dataset and preview its summarized information to get a feel of what i will be working with.
  • Carry out data cleaning.
  • Carry out data analysis.
  • Interpret results.
  • Provide recommendations based on results of analysis.
  • Challenge your solution.

e) Data Relevance

The dataset contains information regarding customer bookings which will aid our research analysis

5.b) Recommendations

From the above analysis, below are our recommendations:

  • Bulk of bookings come from 3 countries [PRT, GBR, FRA]. Greater investment in marketing and promotion in this 3 countries will boost revenue
  • Most popular reserved room types are A and D. Room Types B,C,F,G,H,L have such low demand that management should consid converting them to room types A,D or E
  • The busiest months are July and August. Hotels staffing and resourcing during these months should be optimized to cater for surges in demand with no reduction in service quality due to high customer traffic
  • City Hotels have significantly more bookings than resort hotels. Core business functions should be focused more on the City Hotel side of business than the Resorts
